h4 Constructor and Params

p To create a Tabs Layout, use the constructor:

pre
    code.block.javascript
        | Subtle.TabsLayout(object_id, tabs, params)

p.
    | Where <code>object_id</code> is the id of the parent container and tabs is a list of objects
    | with details on each tab: <code>{div: div_id, icon: html_code_for_icon, label: labe_text}</code>.
    | You can further edit a tabs layout with the following params:

table.params-table
    tr
        td param
        td type
        td default
        td description
    tr
        td show_labels
        td Boolean
        td true
        td Show / hide labels
    tr
        td show_labels_inline
        td Boolean
        td false
        td Show labels on the same line as icons
    tr
        td show_icons
        td Boolean
        td true
        td Show / hide icons
    tr
        td icon_size
        td Number
        td 16
        td Icon size (pixels)
    tr
        td position
        td String ("center", "left", "fill")
        td "center"
        td Position of the tabs
    tr
        td direction
        td String ("horizontal", "vertical")
        td "horizontal"
        td The orientation of the tabs
    tr
        td dock_bottom
        td Boolean
        td false
        td Place the tabs on the bottom of the container (for horizontal direction)
    tr
        td color
        td String (from Subtle.COLORS, hex or rgb)
        td COLORS['primary']
        td Selected tab color
